  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DocumentWriter
    Converts a tree of requirements into a reqif file Limitations: Only supports exactly one SpecObject type.
    GraphWriter
    Write a simple CSV-output of the requirement tree (nodes + edges); may be used used by tools such as gephi This is purely nice-to-have and technically unrelated to the ReqIF-output
    GraphWriter.Edge
    An edge in the resulting graph (links between requirements are mapped to edges)
    GraphWriter.Node
    A node in the resulting graph (requirements will be mapped to nodes)
    ReqifDataType<T>  
    ReqifField<T,V extends TraceableArtifact>
    Represents a single field in the ReqIF output (that is: one line in ProR's properties view)
    ReqifFieldBoolean<V extends TraceableArtifact>
    ReqIF field for booleans
    ReqifFieldEnum<T extends java.lang.Enum<T>,V extends TraceableArtifact>
    ReqIF field for enums
    ReqifFieldProxy
    Special field for proxy requirements (= placeholders for requirements which are outside of the current document)
    SpecHierarchyWriter
    Writer for the hierarchy part of the ReqIF Note: Can only write "singletons" (i.e. one source requirement can only occur once in the output tree)
